New hypotheses added (no changes to existing hypotheses)

H62 - Vendor Agent SDK Safety Primitives (Guardrails move up-stack)
- Thesis: safety and governance primitives are moving into vendor agent SDKs. This accelerates adoption but increases cross-SDK governance needs (policy mapping, evidence export, org baseline) to avoid lock-in.
- Signal: OpenAI Agents SDK update (TechCrunch, 2026-04-15)

H63 - Agent Seat Licensing & Procurement Controls (Agents as employees)
- Thesis: if agents become first-class workers, licensing/seat assignment/entitlements becomes a procurement + compliance control plane. Needs explicit agent principal -> allowed apps/licenses mapping plus audit export.
- Signal: Microsoft exec suggests agents will need to buy licenses (Business Insider, 2026-04-14)

H64 - Integrity Hallucination / Decision Consistency Governance
- Thesis: in high-stakes delegation, the pain is not only hallucination but inconsistent decisions (same input, different output/rationale). Needs decision fingerprinting, invariants, regression suites, and an integrity drift metric.
- Signal: integrity hallucination article (Devdiscourse, 2026-04-15)

Top 3 opportunities + suggested experiments (from the above)

1) Cross-SDK evidence export baseline (H62)
- Why now: vendor guardrails are landing, but buyers want standardized compliance artifacts across SDKs.
- Experiment: 3-day prototype: evidence export adapter for one OpenAI Agents SDK workflow (tool-call timeline + policy decisions + correlation id), designed to map to the same schema for other SDKs.

2) Agent entitlement registry (H63)
- Why now: "agents buy seats" is procurement language, quickly becomes cost + compliance.
- Experiment: 1-week MVP: minimal entitlement registry (agent principal -> allowed SaaS/apps/licenses) + audit export + simple approval flow.

3) Integrity drift check for outbound actions (H64)
- Why now: naming the failure mode makes it buyer-legible; consistency becomes a control requirement in high-stakes systems.
- Experiment: 1-week: integrity test pack (20 fixed scenarios) + regression run before releases, plus runtime invariant checks before outbound email / record updates.

